    "The notation 'C', 'A', 'V', and 'T ' (below) is fromLitak 2005aLitak,b, 2008.",
    "See § 5 for the definitions of these classes of BAOs.",
    "In § 2 and following, we use the symbol '⊑' instead of '≤' for the order relation in possibility frames.",
    "It is also important to note that our notation in this paper is flipped relative to most of the literature on intuitionistic Kripke semantics: we take x ⊑ y to mean that x is a refinement/further specification/extension/etc.",
    "of y (in agreement with most of the literature on set-theoretic forcing, as well asDragalin 1988), whereas much of the intuitionistic literature would take it to mean that y is an extension of x."
